{"id":715183,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Big_Short_(movie)","text":"\"The Big Short\" is a 2015 American biographical comedy-drama film. It was directed by Adam McKay. It was written by McKay and Charles Randolph. It is based on the 2010 book ' by Michael Lewis that shows how the financial crisis of 2007\u20132008 was started by the United States housing bubble. The film stars Christian Bale, Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, Brad Pitt, Melissa Leo, Hamish Linklater, John Magaro, Rafe Spall, Jeremy Strong, Finn Wittrock, and Marisa Tomei.\nThe film had a limited release in the United States on December 11, 2015. It had a wide release on December 23 by Paramount Pictures.\nRelease.\nOn September 22, 2015, Paramount set the film for a limited release on December 11, 2015 and a wide release on December 23, 2015.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Biographical_film","surface_form":"biographical","offset":35},{"uri":"Comedy-drama","surface_form":"comedy-drama","offset":48},{"uri":"Adam_McKay","surface_form":"Adam McKay","offset":86},{"uri":"Charles_Randolph","surface_form":"Charles Randolph","offset":126},{"uri":"Michael_Lewis","surface_form":"Michael Lewis","offset":178},{"uri":"Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008","surface_form":"financial crisis of 2007\u20132008","offset":211},{"uri":"United_States_housing_bubble","surface_form":"United States housing bubble","offset":260},{"uri":"Christian_Bale","surface_form":"Christian Bale","offset":305},{"uri":"Steve_Carell","surface_form":"Steve Carell","offset":321},{"uri":"Ryan_Gosling","surface_form":"Ryan Gosling","offset":335},{"uri":"Brad_Pitt","surface_form":"Brad Pitt","offset":349},{"uri":"Melissa_Leo","surface_form":"Melissa Leo","offset":360},{"uri":"Hamish_Linklater","surface_form":"Hamish Linklater","offset":373},{"uri":"John_Magaro","surface_form":"John Magaro","offset":391},{"uri":"Rafe_Spall","surface_form":"Rafe Spall","offset":404},{"uri":"Jeremy_Strong_(actor)","surface_form":"